-- Bank of Japan October Long-Term Forecasts
-- B y   M a s a h i r o   H i d a k a ,   I s a a c   A q u i n o ,   T o r u   F u j i o k a
-- 2013-10-01T15:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-01/bank-of-japan-october-long-term-forecasts-table-.html
Twenty-six of 36 economists expect the BOJ to add
to easing in the first six months of next year, according to a Bloomberg News
survey carried out between Sept. 26 and Oct. 1. Increasing purchases of
Japanese  government bonds , exchange-traded funds and Japanese real-estate
investment trusts are seen as a next step by many of the economists in the 
survey.                NOTE 1: 2H = 2nd half of the year
NOTE 2: 2Q = 2nd quarter of the year
